<LP>
   DALLAS -- Royal International Optical Corp. said it
scheduled a special meeting for June 28 to allow shareholders
to vote on its proposed merger with U.S. Vision Inc.
   Under the offer, U.S. Vision will acquire 80% of Royal's
stock for $12.50 a share in cash. The remaining shares will
be exchanged for stock in the merged company, which will
operate under Royal International's name.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   In composite trading yesterday on the New York Stock
Exchange, Royal closed at $10.25, up 12.5 cents.
   U.S. Vision is closely held. Both Royal and U.S. Vision,
based in Glendora, N.J., are optical retailers.
</TEXT>
